$ PowerShell cmdLet New-ScheduledTaskTrigger
@ new-scheduledTaskTrigger

`new-scheduledTaskTrigger` creates trigger that is
  • *time-based* (task is started once, daily or weekly at a given time) or
  • *event-based* trigger (task is started when the system boots up, or a user log on/off)

`new-scheduledTaskAction` returns a `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/Microsoft/Management/Infrastructure/CimInstance` object.

sa:
 `→ Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/scheduledTask/register`

  → Windows/services/installed/Schedule#task-scheduler-ps-at-startup
